name: Buffalo Chicken Totchos
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Crispy tater tots piled high with buffalo chicken and cheese for a 'nacho' experience your friends and family will love.  Substitute blue cheese dressing for the ranch if desired.
ingredients: 1 (32 ounce) package frozen bite-size potato nuggets (such as Tater Tots®)
2 pounds boneless skinless chicken breasts, cubed
directions: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C)
Spread potato nuggets in a single layer on a baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 25 minutes
Meanwhile, place chicken in a large bowl
Add celery seed and olive oil
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat
Add chicken and cook until golden brown on all sides, about 15 minutes
Turn heat off and add wing sauce
Set an oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler to low
Spoon chicken mixture evenly over potatoes and top with Monterey Jack cheese
Broil on low until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes
Remove from oven and drizzle ranch dressing over the top
